   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🤖 Task 4: Context-Aware Chatbot Using LangChain & RAG\n",
    "\n",
    "**Internship:** DevelopersHub Corporation — AI/ML Engineering Advanced Internship  \n",
    "**Task:** Build a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) chatbot  \n",
    "**Technologies:** LangChain, FAISS, HuggingFace, Streamlit  \n",
    "**Estimated Time:** 40-60 minutes  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📌 Problem Statement\n",
    "\n",
    "Build a conversational chatbot that:\n",
    "1. **Retrieves relevant documents** from a knowledge base\n",
    "2. **Maintains conversation context** using memory\n",
    "3. **Generates informed answers** using an LLM\n",
    "4. **Cites sources** for transparency\n",
    "5. **Deploys as a web app** for live interaction\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Skills You'll Learn\n",
    "✅ Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)  \n",
    "✅ Vector databases (FAISS)  \n",
    "✅ Document embeddings  \n",
    "✅ Conversation memory management  \n",
    "✅ LLM integration with LangChain  \n",
    "✅ Web deployment with Streamlit  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🗂️ Notebook Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Installation & Setup\n",
    "2. Configuration\n",
    "3. Document Loading & Processing\n",
    "4. Vector Database Creation\n",
    "5. LLM Setup\n",
    "6. RAG Chain Creation\n",
    "7. Interactive Testing\n",
    "8. Conversation Analysis\n",
    "9. Deployment Guide\n",
    "10. Advanced Customization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## ⚙️ Step 1: Installation & Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install required packages\n",
    "# Run once, then comment out\n",
    "\n",
    "!pip install -q \\\n",
    "  langchain \\\n",
    "  langchain-community \\\n",
    "  transformers \\\n",
    "  torch \\\n",
    "  faiss-cpu \\\n",
    "  sentence-transformers \\\n",
    "  streamlit \\\n",
    "  pandas \\\n",
    "  numpy \\\n",
    "  tqdm \\\n",
    "  wikipedia"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Standard imports\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data & visualization\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "\n",
    "# LangChain imports\n",
    "from langchain.document_loaders import TextLoader, DirectoryLoader\n",
    "from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain.embeddings import HuggingFaceEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain.vectorstores import FAISS\n",
    "from langchain.chains import ConversationalRetrievalChain\n",
    "from langchain.memory import ConversationBufferMemory\n",
    "from langchain.llms import HuggingFacePipeline\n",
    "from langchain.schema import Document\n",
    "\n",
    "# Transformers\n",
    "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForCausalLM, pipeline\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ All imports successful!')\n",
    "print(f'   PyTorch: {torch.__version__}')\n",
    "print(f'   CUDA Available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📋 Step 2: Configuration & Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Configuration Dictionary\n",
    "CONFIG = {\n",
    "    # Embedding Model (fast and good quality)\n",
    "    'EMBEDDING_MODEL': 'sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2',\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # LLM Model (try: 'gpt2', 'distilgpt2', 'gpt2-medium')\n",
    "    # For better quality but slower: 'mistral-7b' (requires more memory)\n",
    "    'LLM_MODEL': 'gpt2',\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Text processing\n",
    "    'CHUNK_SIZE': 500,          # Characters per chunk\n",
    "    'CHUNK_OVERLAP': 100,        # Overlap between chunks\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Retrieval\n",
    "    'TOP_K': 3,                 # Number of docs to retrieve\n",
    "    'SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD': 0.6,\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generation\n",
    "    'MAX_LENGTH': 512,\n",
    "    'TEMPERATURE': 0.7,\n",
    "    'TOP_P': 0.9,\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Device\n",
    "    'DEVICE': 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu',\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create directories\n",
    "for dir_name in ['./data', './vectordb', './cache', './logs']:\n",
    "    Path(dir_name).mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Configuration loaded')\n",
    "print(f'   Device: {CONFIG[\"DEVICE\"]}')\n",
    "print(f'   Embedding Model: {CONFIG[\"EMBEDDING_MODEL\"]}')\n",
    "print(f'   LLM Model: {CONFIG[\"LLM_MODEL\"]}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📄 Step 3: Create Sample Documents"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create sample documents for the knowledge base\n",
    "sample_docs = [\n",
    "    Document(\n",
    "        page_content=\"\"\"\n",
    "Artificial Intelligence (AI) is the simulation of human intelligence by machines.\n",
    "AI systems can learn from data, recognize patterns, and make decisions.\n",
    "Applications of AI include:\n",
    "- Natural Language Processing (chatbots, translation)\n",
    "- Computer Vision (image recognition, autonomous vehicles)\n",
    "- Recommendation Systems (Netflix, Amazon)\n",
    "- Healthcare (diagnosis, drug discovery)\n",
    "        \"\"\",\n",
    "        metadata={'source': 'AI Overview', 'topic': 'Technology'}\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Document(\n",
    "        page_content=\"\"\"\n",
    "Machine Learning is a subset of AI where systems learn from data without explicit programming.\n",
    "Types of Machine Learning:\n",
    "1. Supervised Learning - Learning from labeled data\n",
    "   - Regression: Predicting continuous values\n",
    "   - Classification: Categorizing into groups\n",
    "2. Unsupervised Learning - Finding patterns in unlabeled data\n",
    "   - Clustering: Grouping similar items\n",
    "   - Dimensionality Reduction: Simplifying data\n",
    "3. Reinforcement Learning - Learning through trial and reward\n",
    "        \"\"\",\n",
    "        metadata={'source': 'Machine Learning Guide', 'topic': 'ML'}\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Document(\n",
    "        page_content=\"\"\"\n",
    "Deep Learning uses neural networks with multiple layers (hence \"deep\").\n",
    "Key architectures:\n",
    "1. Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) - For image processing\n",
    "   - Extract features from images\n",
    "   - Used in computer vision\n",
    "2. Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) - For sequential data\n",
    "   - Process sequences like text and time series\n",
    "   - Variants: LSTM, GRU\n",
    "3. Transformers - For NLP and sequence modeling\n",
    "   - Attention mechanism\n",
    "   - Models: BERT, GPT, T5\n",
    "        \"\"\",\n",
    "        metadata={'source': 'Deep Learning Guide', 'topic': 'DL'}\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Document(\n",
    "        page_content=\"\"\"\n",
    "Natural Language Processing (NLP) enables computers to understand and generate human language.\n",
    "Key NLP Tasks:\n",
    "1. Text Classification - Categorizing text (sentiment analysis, spam detection)\n",
    "2. Named Entity Recognition - Identifying entities (people, places, organizations)\n",
    "3. Machine Translation - Converting between languages\n",
    "4. Question Answering - Answering questions about documents\n",
    "5. Summarization - Creating concise summaries\n",
    "6. Sentiment Analysis - Determining emotional tone\n",
    "\n",
    "Modern NLP uses Transformer models that have revolutionized the field.\n",
    "        \"\"\",\n",
    "        metadata={'source': 'NLP Tutorial', 'topic': 'NLP'}\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    Document(\n",
    "        page_content=\"\"\"\n",
    "Python is the primary language for AI/ML development.\n",
    "Popular AI/ML Libraries:\n",
    "1. TensorFlow - Deep learning framework by Google\n",
    "   - Keras API for high-level models\n",
    "   - Production deployment\n",
    "2. PyTorch - Dynamic neural network library by Meta\n",
    "   - Pythonic and intuitive\n",
    "   - Research and production\n",
    "3. Scikit-learn - Traditional ML algorithms\n",
    "   - Decision Trees, SVM, Clustering\n",
    "   - Preprocessing and evaluation\n",
    "4. Pandas - Data manipulation\n",
    "5. NumPy - Numerical computing\n",
    "6. Matplotlib/Seaborn - Visualization\n",
    "        \"\"\",\n",
    "        metadata={'source': 'Python Guide', 'topic': 'Programming'}\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✅ Created {len(sample_docs)} sample documents')\n",
    "for i, doc in enumerate(sample_docs, 1):\n",
    "    print(f'   [{i}] {doc.metadata[\"source\"]}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## ✂️ Step 4: Document Chunking"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split documents into chunks for better retrieval\n",
    "print(f\"✂️  Chunking {len(sample_docs)} documents...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size      = CONFIG['CHUNK_SIZE'],\n",
    "    chunk_overlap   = CONFIG['CHUNK_OVERLAP'],\n",
    "    separators      = [\"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \" \", \"\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "chunks = splitter.split_documents(sample_docs)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Created {len(chunks)} chunks\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Avg chunk size: {np.mean([len(c.page_content) for c in chunks]):.0f} chars\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Min chunk size: {min(len(c.page_content) for c in chunks)} chars\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Max chunk size: {max(len(c.page_content) for c in chunks)} chars\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display first chunk\n",
    "print(f\"\\n📄 Sample Chunk:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Source: {chunks[0].metadata['source']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Content: {chunks[0].page_content[:150]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 🔤 Step 5: Initialize Embeddings"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load sentence embeddings model\n",
    "print(f\"🔤 Loading embeddings model: {CONFIG['EMBEDDING_MODEL']}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(\n",
    "    model_name     = CONFIG['EMBEDDING_MODEL'],\n",
    "    model_kwargs   = {'device': CONFIG['DEVICE']},\n",
    "    encode_kwargs  = {'normalize_embeddings': True}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Embeddings model loaded\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test embedding\n",
    "test_embedding = embeddings.embed_query(\"What is AI?\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Embedding dimension: {len(test_embedding)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Sample values: {test_embedding[:5]}...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 🗂️ Step 6: Create FAISS Vector Store"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create FAISS vector database\n",
    "print(f\"🗂️  Creating FAISS vector store from {len(chunks)} chunks...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "vectorstore = FAISS.from_documents(\n",
    "    documents = chunks,\n",
    "    embedding = embeddings\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ FAISS vector store created\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save for later use\n",
    "vectordb_path = './vectordb/faiss_index'\n",
    "vectorstore.save_local(vectordb_path)\n",
    "print(f\"   Saved to: {vectordb_path}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test retrieval\n",
    "test_query = \"What is machine learning?\"\n",
    "retrieved_docs = vectorstore.similarity_search(test_query, k=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n🔍 Test Retrieval for: '{test_query}'\")\n",
    "for i, doc in enumerate(retrieved_docs, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"   [{i}] {doc.metadata['source']}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"       {doc.page_content[:100]}...\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 🤖 Step 7: Initialize LLM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load LLM model\n",
    "print(f\"🤖 Loading LLM: {CONFIG['LLM_MODEL']}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(CONFIG['LLM_MODEL'])\n",
    "if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n",
    "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
    "\n",
    "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    CONFIG['LLM_MODEL'],\n",
    "    torch_dtype = torch.float16 if 'cuda' in CONFIG['DEVICE'] else torch.float32,\n",
    "    device_map  = 'auto' if 'cuda' in CONFIG['DEVICE'] else None,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Model loaded on {CONFIG['DEVICE']}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create pipeline\n",
    "text_pipeline = pipeline(\n",
    "    task         = 'text-generation',\n",
    "    model        = model,\n",
    "    tokenizer    = tokenizer,\n",
    "    max_length   = CONFIG['MAX_LENGTH'],\n",
    "    do_sample    = True,\n",
    "    temperature  = CONFIG['TEMPERATURE'],\n",
    "    top_p        = CONFIG['TOP_P'],\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Wrap in LangChain\n",
    "llm = HuggingFacePipeline(\n",
    "    model_id    = CONFIG['LLM_MODEL'],\n",
    "    task        = 'text-generation',\n",
    "    pipeline    = text_pipeline,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ LLM pipeline created\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 💾 Step 8: Setup Conversation Memory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create conversation memory\n",
    "print(\"💾 Initializing conversation memory...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "memory = ConversationBufferMemory(\n",
    "    memory_key      = 'chat_history',\n",
    "    return_messages = True,\n",
    "    human_prefix    = 'User',\n",
    "    ai_prefix       = 'Assistant',\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Memory initialized\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Type: Buffer Memory\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Max tokens: Unlimited\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## ⛓️ Step 9: Create RAG Chain"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create the RAG conversation chain\n",
    "print(\"⛓️  Creating ConversationalRetrievalChain...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "retriever = vectorstore.as_retriever(\n",
    "    search_type = 'similarity',\n",
    "    search_kwargs = {\n",
    "        'k': CONFIG['TOP_K'],\n",
    "        'score_threshold': CONFIG['SIMILARITY_THRESHOLD']\n",
    "    }\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "qa_chain = ConversationalRetrievalChain.from_llm(\n",
    "    llm             = llm,\n",
    "    retriever       = retriever,\n",
    "    memory          = memory,\n",
    "    return_source_documents = True,\n",
    "    verbose         = True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ RAG chain created successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 💬 Step 10: Interactive Testing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test the chatbot with multiple questions\n",
    "test_questions = [\n",
    "    \"What is artificial intelligence?\",\n",
    "    \"Tell me about machine learning\",\n",
    "    \"What are transformers in deep learning?\",\n",
    "    \"How does NLP work?\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "conversation_history = []\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(\"💬 INTERACTIVE CHATBOT TEST\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70 + \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, question in enumerate(test_questions, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n[Q{i}] User: {question}\")\n",
    "    print(\"-\" * 70)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        # Get response\n",
    "        result = qa_chain(\n",
    "            {'question': question},\n",
    "            return_only_outputs=False\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        answer = result['answer']\n",
    "        source_docs = result.get('source_documents', [])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Store in history\n",
    "        conversation_history.append({\n",
    "            'question': question,\n",
    "            'answer': answer,\n",
    "            'num_sources': len(source_docs),\n",
    "            'sources': [doc.metadata['source'] for doc in source_docs]\n",
    "        })\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Display\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n🤖 Assistant: {answer[:300]}...\\n\")\n",
    "        print(f\"📚 Sources Used ({len(source_docs)}):\")\n",
    "        for j, doc in enumerate(source_docs, 1):\n",
    "            print(f\"   [{j}] {doc.metadata['source']}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"❌ Error: {str(e)}\")\n",
    "        conversation_history.append({\n",
    "            'question': question,\n",
    "            'error': str(e)\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*70)\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Test completed! ({len(conversation_history)} Q&A pairs)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📊 Step 11: Conversation Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analyze conversation\n",
    "print(\"📊 CONVERSATION ANALYSIS\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to DataFrame\n",
    "conv_df = pd.DataFrame(conversation_history)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(conv_df.to_string())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n📈 Statistics:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Total Q&A: {len(conv_df)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Avg sources per Q: {conv_df['num_sources'].mean():.1f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Min sources: {conv_df['num_sources'].min()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Max sources: {conv_df['num_sources'].max()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize source usage\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sources per question\n",
    "ax1.bar(range(len(conv_df)), conv_df['num_sources'], color='skyblue', edgecolor='navy')\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('Question')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('Number of Sources')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Sources Retrieved per Question')\n",
    "ax1.set_xticks(range(len(conv_df)))\n",
    "ax1.set_xticklabels([f'Q{i+1}' for i in range(len(conv_df))])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Source popularity\n",
    "all_sources = []\n",
    "for sources_list in conv_df['sources']:\n",
    "    if isinstance(sources_list, list):\n",
    "        all_sources.extend(sources_list)\n",
    "\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "source_counts = Counter(all_sources)\n",
    "\n",
    "if source_counts:\n",
    "    ax2.barh(list(source_counts.keys()), list(source_counts.values()), color='lightcoral', edgecolor='darkred')\n",
    "    ax2.set_xlabel('Frequency')\n",
    "    ax2.set_title('Source Document Popularity')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('conversation_analysis.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Analysis plot saved as conversation_analysis.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 💾 Step 12: Save & Export"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],\n",
    "source": [
    "# Save conversation to JSON\n",
    "export_data = {\n",
    "    'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(),\n",
    "    'config': CONFIG,\n",
    "    'conversation': conversation_history,\n",
    "    'statistics': {\n",
    "        'total_messages': len(conv_df),\n",
    "        'avg_sources': float(conv_df['num_sources'].mean()),\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "export_path = f'./logs/conversation_{datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")}.json'\n",
